Ode Χ.

⁴To Mercury, as the Latin representative of the Greek Hermes.

Subject. The prerogatives and attributes of the god and his services to mankind. Porphyrion says the ode is imitated from Alcaeus.

Metre. Sapphic. 1. On the caesura, see Introd. p. xxix.

facunde, λόγιος. Cf. Martial vn. 74. 1 Cyllenes caelique decus, facunde minister. Mr Page aptly quotes Acts 14. 12 ‘And they called Barnabas Jupiter and Paul Mercury‚ because he was the chief speaker.'
